node.text: California Gov. Gavin Newsom snapped at reporters last week and said that critics are “b****ing” about the Golden State because of its success. Newsom, who was widely criticized for violating his own draconian COVID policies, is facing a close recall election in September. TONIGHT on “Hannity,” Leo “2.0” Terrell and Ari Fleischer will discuss Newsom’s failures and the recall.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Sean Hannity on August 11, 2021 tagging @mensahtamyrastock. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'ONE-ON-ONE WITH OLYMPIC GOLD MEDALIST TAMYRA MENSAH-STOCK Photo di AP Pho Favila USA Hannity'.

node.text: Olympic gold medalist Tamyra Mensah-Stock went viral for expressing her love of America after winning in Tokyo. "I love representing the U.S. I freaking love living there," Mensah-Stock told reporters. TONIGHT on “Hannity,” we’ll talk to Mensah-Stock about the Olympics, representing America and her future. Tune in at 9 PM ET or set your DVR for this must-see interview!
